# ‚úÖ **Why this structure is conventional**

Modern .NET projects typically follow the **Domain / Application / Infrastructure** separation.
This helps your program scale and makes responsibility boundaries very clear.

---

# üìå **1. Domain Layer (Your Entities & Core Logic)**

> Contains **entities, models, and business rules** ONLY.

You did this correctly already, your entities are well structured.
What you were missing was grouping them inside an overall **Domain folder**:

### **Folder: Domain/Base**

* `BaseEntity.cs`
  *Your abstract root entity ‚Äî perfect.*

### **Folder: Domain/SchoolMembers**

* `SchoolMember.cs` (abstract second-degree)
* `Student.cs`
* `Teacher.cs`

### **Folder: Domain/Courses**

* `Course.cs`
* `Subject.cs`

### Why this is good

* Keeps all data models in one place
* Matches ‚Äúclean architecture‚Äù conventions
* Scales very well when you add more features

---

# üìå **2. Application Layer (Menu, Programs, Use Cases)**

This contains the *logic of how the system works*, not how data is stored.

### Examples:

* Menu interactions
* Creation programs for courses and subjects
* Orchestration logic (high-level)

### Folder: `Application/CourseProgram`

Your existing content goes here.

### Folder: `Application/Menu`

`Menu.cs` moves here.

### File: `Application/Program.cs`

The entry point (`Main`, setup, loop) stays here.

---

# üìå **3. Infrastructure Layer (FileManager, Database, JSON Files)**

> Handles communication with **external systems**.

Your `FileManager` is a perfect example of infrastructure.

### Folder: `Infrastructure/FileManager`

* `FileManager.cs`

### Folder: `Infrastructure/Data`

* All `.json` files
* Nothing else (no logic here ‚Äî only storage)

### Why this matches conventions:

* Infrastructure code can be replaced (e.g., JSON ‚Üí SQL DB)
* Domain does not depend on data storage
* High maintainability

---

# üéØ **What improves with this structure?**

### ‚úî Clear separation of responsibilities

Domain = WHAT the app is about
Application = HOW the app behaves
Infrastructure = HOW it is stored

### ‚úî Easier to scale

Want to add:

* Logging? ‚Üí Infrastructure/Logging
* API? ‚Üí Infrastructure/Api
* Web UI? ‚Üí Application/Web

All clean and organized.

### ‚úî Professional & conventional

Matches typical .NET project layout used in companies.

---

# üìå **Extra optional improvements**

### **Add namespaces matching folders:**

Example:

```csharp
namespace StudentFinal.Domain.SchoolMembers;
namespace StudentFinal.Infrastructure.FileManager;
namespace StudentFinal.Application.Menu;
```

This is standard and strongly recommended.

---

